external_knowledge:
Season refers to the period of the year when the league is active and teams compete against each other; 
A win-loss record is a tally of the number of wins and losses a team has experienced; 
A victory margin is the difference in score by which a match was won; 
Opponent rating is a measure of the strength or skill level of the opposing team, often based on past performances.

- A "completed" match refers to a match that has finished and has a determined outcome; 
- The "average margin" is a measure of a team's performance, with higher values indicating better performance; 
- The time frame of "the past three months" is determined based on the current date.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) AS successful_predictions_count
FROM model_predictions mp
WHERE mp.predicted_outcome = mp.actual_outcome;

